The test_files module
=====================

	>>> import test_files
	>>> print test_files.__doc__
	This module provides convenience methids to handle test files
	...

The module provides a method which gets all possible test files
	which means *.tests, *.test, *.py, in that order

We expect to find such extensions for this file here
	>>> scripts_here = test_files.get_test_scripts([], False)
	>>> test_files_here = [ ts.basename() for ts in scripts_here if 'test_files' in ts]
	>>> 'test_files.test' in test_files_here
	True

The method can also take arguments to search directories recursively
	and args is a list of possible stems 
	>>> stems = [ 'test_files', 'try' ]
	>>> stemmed_scripts = [ ts.basename() for ts in test_files.get_test_scripts(args=stems, recursive=False) ]
	>>> 'test_files.test' in stemmed_scripts and 'try.py' in stemmed_scripts
	True
